snippet.textDisplay: I kind of 2019 my bitch so 2020 is my “okay calm down” year. I also graduated college which was super exciting but I was very sick the second half of 2018 and all of 2019. I was in and out of the ER and different specialists and I got so tired of faking I was okay when actually I had a sizable tumor in my uterus destroying my life. So in 2019 I decided fuck it, I am not faking anything. So whenever someone would ask me “are you okay?” Or “how are you feeling?” I’d say no, I’m not okay. Or I don’t feel well. I would give a blunt answer. And people would look at me like I’m crazy but I did feel like shit all the time and they weren’t expecting a real answer. I had surgery to remove the tumor last week so 2020 is my year of okay reel it in. We’ve been sick for a while but now we have no excuse to be a dick. It’s also my year to leave my shitty retail safety net job and get a real job that pertains to my degree and I’m so hyped.

snippet.textDisplay: I moved out of my moms house at 18, then lived with my dad a little bit then finally on my own. By the end of the 3 years that I lived solo I didn’t know who I was lol, I kinda disassociated from who I was and from the world. I spent my teens saying “I’ll find myself when I’m older”, boy was I wrong! I spent my YA years working and going to school I neglected myself. Self care, who’s she? I’m slowly finding myself again, a new and improved me.
